 'Paul Kiranga is a Co-Founder and the Partner in charge of the Bank Securities and Conveyancing Department at SOKLaw. He holds a Bachelor of Laws (LL.B) degree from the University of Nairobi (2009) and a Postgraduate Diploma in Law from the Kenya School of Law (2010). He was admitted to the Roll of Advocates in 2011. Paul has gained extensive experience in real estate and conveyancing practice, as well as the perfection of securities. He previously served as an associate in charge of the Conveyancing and Bank Securities Department at Mucheru-Oyatta & Associates Advocates, where he perfected security documents on behalf of major banks in Kenya, including Bank of Baroda (K) Limited, Standard Chartered Bank (K) Limited, and Guardian Bank Kenya Limited. In addition to banking and conveyancing, Paul has significant experience in corporate and commercial law, advising on mergers and acquisitions, joint ventures, capital markets, structured financing, intellectual property, aircraft leasing & financing, and energy law. He has successfully acted for leading Kenyan and international corporate clients.', 
